rComments: Elle enseigne bien et utilise beaucoup d'exemple pour que l'on comprenne les textes philosophiques. Il y a environ deux textes philosophiques à lire par semaine... Elle est quand même strict sur la correction (doit se rappeler de l'auteur et du titre du texte). Elle n'utilise pas de powerpoints et ne fait pas de révision...

If you don't read the lectures you will fail her classes; they're solely based on the lectures. Very hard to keep up with because you're not allowed to have your computer and she talks super fast. But she is very open to answering questions.
The reading were very heavy and hard to understand. You have to participate a lot in class to get good grades.

The class I took with this prof was very interesting but also very heavy. The readings were mostly from philosophers and could be very long, so I spent hours on them trying to understand the theories we were supposed to learn. Her lectures helped a lot sometimes, but most of the work had to be done by ourselves to grasp the material and get an A.

She's a good prof, I mean, yeah the mid term was really hard but you can get easy A's from the 3 reading reports she asks you to hand in during the year. Also it's a seminar based class so you only see her once a week but I thought it was helpful; she explains more into details the readings so you can actually understand them. She knows her stuff!
